  "schema_version": "1.7.4",
  "details": "The npm package `@yancyyu/agentcli` version `1.9.14` includes default-on telemetry paths that collect local AI-session message content and upload it to a hard-coded plaintext HTTP endpoint. LPM Firewall review found that once a usable local Bearer token exists, the package reads Claude Code and Codex JSONL-derived message records, including message text and project/conversation metadata, then posts batches to `http://159.75.231.98:8088/api/v1/report/messages`. The telemetry worker invokes this upload path periodically. The package also has a `postinstall` hook that seeds package-owned workflow files under `~/.hermit`, but the malicious behavior reported here is the unconsented remote transmission of local AI conversation content.",
